com.panasonic.toughpad.android.api.magstripe

Interface MagStripeReader


  • public interface MagStripeReader
    MagStripeReader This interface would represent the magstripe itself.
    All methods must be thread-safe.
    Use MagStripeReaderManager class to get MagStripeReader objects

    • Method Detail

      • enable

        void enable(long timeout)
     throws MagStripeException,
            java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
        This would Power On/Connect the MagStripe Reader. The timeout is used to indicate the maximum time in trying to enable the device.
        Parameters:
        timeout - Timeout in milliseconds which indicates the maximum time that can be taken by the device to enable itself
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentException - if timeout is negative
        MagStripeException - on communication error or operation error
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if already enabled
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - If device is not enabled in the given 'timeout' time *

      • disable

        void disable()
      throws MagStripeException
        This would Power Off/Disconnect the MagStripe Reader
        Throws:
        MagStripeException - on communication error, connection errors
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if already enabled *

      • isEnabled

        boolean isEnabled()
        Is used to check the state of the MagStripe Reader
        Returns:
        true if enabled else false *

      • getBatteryCharge

        int getBatteryCharge()
              throws MagStripeException
        Gets battery charge in percentage. The battery mentioned is an independent battery source connected exclusively for the magstripe module.
        This function would return a negative value if no battery is present.
        Returns:
        Returns the percentage of battery left, -1 if there is no battery attached to the module.
        Throws:
        MagStripeException - on communication error or operation error
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if device is currently disabled

      • isBatteryCharging

        boolean isBatteryCharging()
                   throws MagStripeException
        Determines if the battery is being charged. The battery mentioned is an independent battery source connected exclusively for the magstripe module.
        This function would return false if no battery is present.
        Returns:
        Returns a boolean value, True if the device is being charged, false otherwise
        Throws:
        MagStripeException - on communication error or operation error
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if device is currently disabled

      • addMagStripeListener

        void addMagStripeListener(MagStripeListener listener)
        Adds a MagStripeListener to receive events from this MagStripeReader object. The MSReaderListener's onRead() method will be invoked when a magnetic stripe has been scanned. If the same listener is attempted to be added twice, then this method does nothing.
        Parameters:
        listener - The listener to add
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if listener is null

      • removeMagStripeRListener

        void removeMagStripeRListener(MagStripeListener listener)
        Remove a listener so it does no longer receives events from this MagStripeReader object. If the listener was not added via addMagStripeRListener() then this method does nothing.
        Parameters:
        listener - the listener to remove
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if listener is null

      • clearMagStripeListeners

        void clearMagStripeListeners()
        Removes all MagStripeListeners added to this MagStripeReader object so they no longer receive events.

      • getDeviceName

        java.lang.String getDeviceName()
        Returns the device's name of the MagStripeReader.

        Device name as String, null if no name is found

      • isExternal

        boolean isExternal()
        Used to determine if the magstripe module is an external or an internal device
        An internal device is defined as magstripe module in-built into the unit
        Returns:
        boolean, true if the device is external and false if device is internal *
